Register the hello-world executable as the CTest test hello_world_debug_output and add rcfile fixtures that make the override behavior deterministic: use LIBCWD_RCFILE_OVERRIDE_NAME=$REPOROOT/testsuite/ctest/support/libcwdrc_hello-override, add a minimal readable base rcfile such as support/libcwdrc_hello-base because read_rcfile first opens a primary rcfile, and set LIBCWD_RCFILE_NAME to that base. The base should suppress rcfile diagnostics and establish a known default state; the override should leave BFD, DEBUG, HELLO, and SYSTEM enabled while NOTICE and WARNING are disabled.
